[sinister music playing]

250
00:14:38,085 --> 00:14:39,712
He almost crushed my foot.

251
00:14:41,755 --> 00:14:44,466
Boss, do you think he went in here?

252
00:14:44,550 --> 00:14:45,593
Naturally.

253
00:14:46,093 --> 00:14:48,053
That’s why we’re hanging out outside.

254
00:14:49,138 --> 00:14:52,182
When we see him, we’ll peel his skin,

255
00:14:52,266 --> 00:14:54,518
so he knows who he’s messing with.

256
00:14:54,602 --> 00:14:56,729
[Ibyang chuckles]

257
00:14:56,812 --> 00:14:58,147
This is funny.

258
00:14:58,230 --> 00:15:01,150
[indistinct chattering on TV]

259
00:15:01,233 --> 00:15:02,943
Oh, sis!

260
00:15:03,444 --> 00:15:05,446
Have you been standing there for a while?

261
00:15:05,529 --> 00:15:07,323
You might grow veins.

262
00:15:07,406 --> 00:15:08,699
Why don’t you sit down?

263
00:15:09,199 --> 00:15:10,117
[woman 1 on TV] <i>What's this?</i>

264
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:11,744
I’m fine here.

265
00:15:11,827 --> 00:15:14,038
[woman 1 on TV] <i>Many are waiting</i>
<i>for your dance.</i>

266
00:15:14,121 --> 00:15:16,624
- [woman 2 on TV] <i>Dance?</i>
- [woman 1 on TV] <i>Are you out of it, sis?</i>

267
00:15:16,707 --> 00:15:17,625
[woman 1 on TV] <i>Why don’t you know</i>
<i>what to do?</i>

268
00:15:17,708 --> 00:15:19,209
Is your name Karla?

269
00:15:20,711 --> 00:15:23,213
[funky music playing]

270
00:15:23,297 --> 00:15:25,090
Why do you look like Karlo?

271
00:15:25,174 --> 00:15:26,467
Are you a lesbian?

272
00:15:26,550 --> 00:15:28,552
No. Eh, it’s just my style.

273
00:15:28,636 --> 00:15:30,596
- Is that forbidden?
- No!

274
00:15:31,430 --> 00:15:33,182
I was just checking.

275
00:15:33,265 --> 00:15:36,685
But that get-up doesn’t suit you.

276
00:15:36,769 --> 00:15:37,811
You know…

277
00:15:38,604 --> 00:15:39,855
You could be cute.

278
00:15:40,856 --> 00:15:44,360
But you’re a know-it-all.
Plus, you’re a scammer.

279
00:15:44,443 --> 00:15:47,154
Sis Karla, relax!

280
00:15:47,237 --> 00:15:49,698
I won’t steal from Mr. Grumpy

281
00:15:49,782 --> 00:15:54,536
because he’s going to help me
bring back my sister Ame.

282
00:15:54,620 --> 00:15:55,913
[somber music playing]

283
00:15:55,996 --> 00:15:59,375
I really think she was kidnapped.

284
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:02,544
She wouldn’t just disappear like that.

285
00:16:02,628 --> 00:16:04,672
Why would they kidnap your sister?

286
00:16:04,755 --> 00:16:05,965
You’re not rich.

287
00:16:06,048 --> 00:16:08,008
I don’t know either.

288
00:16:09,677 --> 00:16:10,594
[Karla] Oh!

289
00:16:11,261 --> 00:16:13,263
Maybe the syndicate took your sister…

290
00:16:13,347 --> 00:16:14,181
[tense music]

291
00:16:14,264 --> 00:16:16,350
Took her kidney,

292
00:16:16,850 --> 00:16:18,852
her eyes, her teeth…

293
00:16:18,936 --> 00:16:20,479
and sold them!

294
00:16:21,146 --> 00:16:23,691
And you’ll never see
your sister Ame again.

295
00:16:23,774 --> 00:16:26,860
[indistinct chattering on TV]

296
00:16:31,115 --> 00:16:35,327
[whimpers] That’s what happened
to Mister Temyo.

297
00:16:39,456 --> 00:16:40,666
[whimpers] Lord…

298
00:16:40,749 --> 00:16:44,086
Please don’t let that happen to my sister.

299
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:46,380
Please, Lord.

300
00:16:50,050 --> 00:16:53,053
Hey… I was just joking, just joking!

301
00:16:53,137 --> 00:16:54,805
Sorry, sorry.

302
00:16:55,764 --> 00:16:57,766
Brother Atoy will find your sister.

303
00:16:58,267 --> 00:17:01,812
Brother Atoy is an expert.
No matter the size, he’ll find it.

304
00:17:03,647 --> 00:17:07,443
You’ll see your sister again, okay?

305
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:15,409
- [crowd cheering]
- Fight! Ame, fight!

306
00:17:15,492 --> 00:17:16,910
[Bebang] Fight!

307
00:17:16,994 --> 00:17:18,620
[Bebang] Hurry, fight!

308
00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:19,872
[Bebang] Fight!

309
00:17:20,497 --> 00:17:22,624
[Bebang] Fight! Fight!

310
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:25,335
- [crowd clamoring]
- [Bebang] Oh, jab! Oh, hurry up!

311
00:17:25,419 --> 00:17:26,545
[Bebang] Go, Ame!

312
00:17:27,087 --> 00:17:27,921
[Bebang] Ame, fight!

313
00:17:28,005 --> 00:17:30,799
- [tense music playing]
- [crowd exclaiming]

314
00:17:30,883 --> 00:17:32,342
You’re fighting now, huh.

315
00:17:32,426 --> 00:17:33,552
That’s what I like!

316
00:17:33,635 --> 00:17:35,763
[Bebang] Go!

317
00:17:35,846 --> 00:17:37,806
- [crowd exclaiming]
- [Bebang] Go, hit her! Hit her!

318
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:39,767
[Bebang gasps] Oh! Oh, Ame!

319
00:17:39,850 --> 00:17:42,269
Fight! Fight back!

320
00:17:42,352 --> 00:17:44,563
[Bebang] Don’t cry there!
Pull yourself together!

321
00:17:44,646 --> 00:17:45,481
Pull yourself together, hurry!

322
00:17:45,564 --> 00:17:47,691
Fight! Fight!

323
00:17:47,775 --> 00:17:50,027
Fight! Fight!

324
00:17:50,110 --> 00:17:52,112
- [Bebang] Punch!
- [Ame grunting]

325
00:17:52,196 --> 00:17:54,656
- [Bebang] There!
- [Ame] Sorry! I didn’t mean it!

326
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:56,075
I’m really sorry!

327
00:17:56,158 --> 00:17:57,076
"Sorry"?

328
00:17:57,159 --> 00:17:58,952
Apologize to your face!

329
00:17:59,703 --> 00:18:05,417
[crowd clamoring]

330
00:18:05,501 --> 00:18:06,418
[Ame shrieks]

331
00:18:06,502 --> 00:18:08,712
[crowd cheering]

332
00:18:08,796 --> 00:18:10,339
Ame, fight!

333
00:18:10,422 --> 00:18:13,133
Stand up! Get up, Ame!

334
00:18:13,634 --> 00:18:15,177
- [pensive music playing]
- [Bebang] Fight, Ame!

335
00:18:15,677 --> 00:18:17,179
Ame, fight!

336
00:18:17,763 --> 00:18:19,223
Get up!

337
00:18:23,644 --> 00:18:24,812
[upbeat music playing]

338
00:18:24,895 --> 00:18:26,939
- Do you want more?
- [in English] Yes, please.

339
00:18:34,196 --> 00:18:35,489
I’ll just go to the CR, okay?
Order something.

340
00:18:35,572 --> 00:18:36,490
- [in English] Sure.
- [in English] Excuse me.

341
00:18:41,078 --> 00:18:43,122
Do you think he knows
what I did to his father,

342
00:18:43,205 --> 00:18:44,998
that’s why he came to see me?

343
00:18:45,999 --> 00:18:49,461
Boss, if he knew you were the one
who hit his father and ran,

344
00:18:49,545 --> 00:18:50,587
he would’ve come back
for you a long time ago.

345
00:18:51,171 --> 00:18:52,714
Why would he hang out
in a place like this?

346
00:18:53,549 --> 00:18:55,217
[in English] He can’t afford this place.

347
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:56,635
He’s just the son of a tailor.

348
00:18:57,302 --> 00:19:00,347
[upbeat music continues]

349
00:19:03,267 --> 00:19:04,560
That’s Atoy, huh.

350
00:19:04,643 --> 00:19:05,644
Where?

351
00:19:06,603 --> 00:19:07,938
- Where?
- There, look.

352
00:19:09,481 --> 00:19:10,399
[Red] Let’s go to him.

353
00:19:11,817 --> 00:19:12,651
‪[Red grunts]

354
00:19:14,653 --> 00:19:18,782
[foreboding music playing]

355
00:19:19,366 --> 00:19:21,827
[tense music playing]

356
00:19:30,919 --> 00:19:34,047
[man grunting]

357
00:19:36,592 --> 00:19:38,510
[man 1] Bebang picked a weak one.

358
00:19:38,594 --> 00:19:40,888
- [man 2, indistinct]
- [man 1] Next fight, she’s done for.

359
00:19:43,348 --> 00:19:45,434
Hey! Hey, my cigarette!

360
00:19:46,143 --> 00:19:52,816
[uneasy music playing]

361
00:20:10,918 --> 00:20:13,212
[tense unsettling music playing]

362
00:21:05,138 --> 00:21:07,182
Why didn’t you lock it?
She managed to escape.

363
00:21:07,266 --> 00:21:08,725
[man 1] You’re so careless!

364
00:21:12,980 --> 00:21:14,648
- [man 2] Come on, hurry.
- [man 1] Quick!

365
00:21:49,516 --> 00:21:52,269
We shouldn’t have left. Now she scaped!

366
00:21:52,352 --> 00:21:55,188
Let’s split up.
If you see her, grab her, okay?

367
00:22:04,656 --> 00:22:07,242
Wait. Did you see a midget woman?

368
00:22:07,743 --> 00:22:08,660
No.

369
00:22:10,245 --> 00:22:12,539
You’re in trouble. Looks like
she fled from you again, huh.

370
00:22:18,545 --> 00:22:22,716
[sinister unsettling music playing]

371
00:22:38,148 --> 00:22:41,568
[energetic club music playing]

372
00:22:42,319 --> 00:22:43,153
Why?

373
00:22:44,321 --> 00:22:45,155
Just mistaken identity.

374
00:22:45,238 --> 00:22:50,744
[energetic club music playing]

375
00:22:52,329 --> 00:22:53,246
So? Where?

376
00:22:54,164 --> 00:22:55,248
Nowhere, sir.

377
00:22:55,332 --> 00:22:57,667
There were too many people.
It’s Wednesday, after all.

378
00:22:58,960 --> 00:23:00,962
What does Wednesday have to do with it?
Are we in Baclaran?

379
00:23:02,005 --> 00:23:03,256
Find him.

380
00:23:03,340 --> 00:23:04,841
[indistinct lively chattering]

381
00:23:11,431 --> 00:23:15,894
[tense sinister music playing]

382
00:23:40,710 --> 00:23:42,462
[brazen music playing]

383
00:23:51,471 --> 00:23:52,305
‪[tense music playing]

384
00:23:53,890 --> 00:23:56,434
[breathing heavily]

385
00:24:03,942 --> 00:24:05,986
‪[breathing heavily, whimpers]

386
00:24:18,623 --> 00:24:20,125
Brother… [muffled screams]

387
00:24:21,334 --> 00:24:22,961
[door rattles]

388
00:24:23,837 --> 00:24:25,422
- [latch rattling]
- [muffled screams]

389
00:24:26,006 --> 00:24:26,923
[rattling]

390
00:24:28,216 --> 00:24:30,177
[sinister music playing]

391
00:24:58,705 --> 00:25:00,957
[music intensifies]

392
00:25:12,719 --> 00:25:14,304
Ame was here earlier.

393
00:25:14,387 --> 00:25:17,474
[unsettling music playing]

394
00:25:32,489 --> 00:25:33,490
Psst!

395
00:25:34,741 --> 00:25:35,784
Why are you here?

396
00:25:38,828 --> 00:25:40,747
Now, show me how tough you are.

397
00:25:40,830 --> 00:25:42,749
[brazen music playing]

398
00:25:53,301 --> 00:25:54,636
- [upbeat music playing]
- [grunting]

399
00:25:55,887 --> 00:25:56,721
‪[grunting and groaning]

400
00:26:08,191 --> 00:26:11,152
‪[grunting and groaning]

401
00:26:14,948 --> 00:26:16,825
[screams and grunts]

402
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:19,619
‪[grunting and groaning]

403
00:26:21,288 --> 00:26:25,625
[tense music playing]

404
00:26:27,544 --> 00:26:28,586
[Atoy groans loudly]

405
00:26:29,337 --> 00:26:31,131
You animal, you’re making
it harder for us.

406
00:26:32,382 --> 00:26:33,883
‪[brazen music playing]

407
00:26:34,884 --> 00:26:36,594
[electronic blipping]

408
00:26:36,678 --> 00:26:39,222
[intense music playing]

409
00:26:46,062 --> 00:26:49,774
[grunting, groaning, shouting]

410
00:26:49,858 --> 00:26:53,153
NEXT

411
00:26:58,408 --> 00:27:00,910
This job could get us killed!

412
00:27:00,994 --> 00:27:02,329
But better than having no job, right?

413
00:27:02,412 --> 00:27:04,122
I hope Big Brother comes back.

414
00:27:04,205 --> 00:27:07,042
Maybe he’ll help me get out of here.

415
00:27:07,125 --> 00:27:10,003
I need a disguise
to get inside Endless Nights.

416
00:27:10,086 --> 00:27:14,341
Ask Tonet. I saw she has talent in makeup.

417
00:27:14,424 --> 00:27:15,633
[Cita] <i>Maybe she can help you.</i>

418
00:27:15,717 --> 00:27:17,635
- Jeffrey Matulak.
- [Atoy] Boss…

419
00:27:20,096 --> 00:27:21,222
Present, ma’am.

420
00:27:21,306 --> 00:27:22,682
NEXT

421
00:27:28,521 --> 00:27:29,564
Subtitle translation by:
